   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Lilongwe &amp; Districts CEC</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims at developing an efficient and sustainable system for delivery of eye care services through the Primary Eye Care Strategy (PEC), focusing on two major objectives:

1. To Promote and demonstrate Primary Eye Care as a means of cost effective delivery of eye health services.
2. To strengthen systems for effective integration of eye health into district health plans;

With the following key activities:
&#xD8; Capacity building of health workers &#x2013; equipping them with knowledge and skills in Primary Eye Care. 
&#xD8; Strengthening referral protocols for eye health services.
&#xD8; Provision of vital supplies and support for surgeries.
&#xD8; Provision of eye surgical equipment for district hospital theatres. 
&#xD8; Advocacy for District Health Offices to fully integrate eye health services into district health plans. 

The following outcomes are expected:
&#xD8; Integration of eye health into the district health systems 
&#xD8; Increased uptake of eye care services by community members
&#xD8; Strengthened role of communities and their institutions in delivery of and demand for eye health services</narrative>
  </description>
